cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the security and codifying issues of smart contracts, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also explores the development and usage of smart contracts, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the tokenization of assets, which could be categorized under digital libraries (cs.DL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
